    <!-- The contents of <statement></statement> should specify
         the task you wish them to complete. -->
    <statement>
        <p>
Explain how to find the following for the function <m>f(x)=-x^{3} - 18 \, x^{2} - 105 \, x - 6</m>.
        </p>
        <ol>
            <li>
                <p>
The open intervals where <m>f(x)</m> is increasing or decreasing.
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
The relative extrema of <m>f(x)</m>.
                </p>
            </li>
        </ol>
    </statement>

    <answer>
        <ol>
            <li>
                <p>
The function decreases on <m>(-\infty,-7)</m>,
increases on <m>(-7,-5)</m>, and decreases on
<m>(-5,\infty)</m>.
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
The point <m>(x,y)=(-7,190)</m> is a relative minimum,
and the point <m>(x,y)=(-5,194)</m> is a relative maximum.
                </p>
            </li>
        </ol>
    </answer>
</exercise>
